				Im not a warrior but I was introduced to this mad thirst for crafted armor while in MM (Mistmoore).  Basically u gather items combined with gems or whatever and give them to the crafted armor creator in Karana.  Every piece requires different items to create it.  Example..in mistmoore u needed to kill the werewolf and get its talon combined with about 600pp (give or take a few hundre pp) of gems and u hand it to that centaur fella in karana and he gives u the chest piece.<BR>
<BR>
I see this as an awesome warrior quest as it is warrior only armor.  The reason u see it at merchants is cause many non warrior pcs do this quest for various pcs and sell them to the merchants cause they are getting awesome coin for it and cause they are so high dont want to bother with the hassle of selling it to other players for that extra pp when they can just run the quest again over and over cause they are strong enough to do it. <BR>
<BR>
Also as a side note...quite a few of the key items..ie the werewolf talons for example are no drop items..so if u are not there to loot that corpse of the critter who has your item, then someone else is getting that item and will have to do the quest for u or destroy the item.  This is why I say its a great warrior quest. =)  since so many of these items are no drop.
